From spike QD-14840: HybridCRT linker invocation for SubstrateVM on Windows.

Switches the cl.exe/link.exe invocation from /MD (dynamic CRT, pulls vcruntime140.dll) to /MT
(static CRT, no DLL dependency on vcruntime), while keeping UCRT dynamic via the ucrt.lib import
lib (which loads ucrtbase.dll at runtime — ships with Windows 10 1803+ / Server 2016+).

Per Microsoft's HybridCRT spec
(https://github.com/microsoft/WindowsAppSDK/blob/main/docs/Coding-Guidelines/HybridCRT.md):
  Release: /MT + /NODEFAULTLIB:libucrt.lib + /defaultlib:ucrt.lib

Note: the original `/NODEFAULTLIB:LIBCMT` directive is intentionally REMOVED. With /MD that
directive was preventing the static CRT from being pulled in by mistake; with /MT we WANT LIBCMT
(it provides libvcruntime and libcpmt statically).

The original code's comment "Must use /MD in order to link with JDK native libraries built that
way" describes the JDK-side /MD constraint. Task 0.7 of the QD-14840 runbook empirically tests
whether SubstrateVM-only HybridCRT is sufficient or whether the JDK also needs to be rebuilt
with HybridCRT.

Target file: substratevm/src/com.oracle.svm.hosted/src/com/oracle/svm/hosted/image/CCLinkerInvocation.java
Repo: oracle/graal, branch release/graal-vm/25.0, base commit dbf49c84 ("release GraalVM 25.0.3")

